On 29 September, 2008, a bomb strapped to a motorcycle exploded near a mosque in Malegaon, Maharashtra during the month of Ramzan, just before Navratri. 6 people were killed, over 100 injured. The Maharashtra ATS found that the IED was planted on an LML Freedom bike. The bikes registration led to Sadhvi Pragya Singh Thakur, a former BJP MP. She was arrested in October 2008. 11 people, including Lt Col Purohit, were arrested. The ATS alleged the accused were part of Abhinav Bharat, a radical group. They said the attack was carried out in revenge against terrorist acts by Muslim men. Among the seven on trial, former BJP MOP Sadhvi Pragya and Lt Col Purohit emerged as the most prominent and controversial accused in the case. The NIA said: The bike allegedly involved in the blast did not have a clear chassis number; the probe did not prove it was in Pragya Thakurs possession immediately before the blast. Lt Col Purohit, an Indian Army officer, accused of providing logistical and material. Investigators claimed Purohit helped arrange explosives and was part of meetings where attacks were allegedly planned. Regarding charges against Lt. Col Purohit, the Court found that there was no evidence to prove that he sourced RDX from Kashmir or that he assembled the bomb. Final verdict of the court -- Prosecution has failed to bring any cogent evidence and the evidence is riddled with inconsistencies Terrorism has no religion but conviction cannot be based on moral grounds.

It is through education that you can change the world and break out of the cycle of poverty. The National Sample Survey (NSS-2014) shows that more than two crore Indian children still are out of school after 70 years of independence. Besides being denied an education, these children have also lost their childhood because they must work for their livelihood. This disparity is unfair and undemocratic and hence, Apne Log was founded by a group of dedicated people working together to promote free educational opportunities for underprivileged children living on the streets or in slums. As the name suggests, Apne Log is all about our people, our trust, our belief and our common goal. We strive to not only acknowledge the dire need to educate our children, but also leave no stone unturned to catering to all their needs regardless of their financial circumstances. We are driven by our motto that education is a fundamental right and that no child should be deprived of this right. This ethos has kept our wheels turning for six years now. Over time, education has become institutionalized and commodified. This makes it difficult for underprivileged groups to pursue learning - a barrier that Apne Log plans to eliminate, a barrier that should have never existed in the first place, a barrier that needs to be taken out of the equation. #WriterEditorDirector-#RajKumar#Bhawna_Media For making documentary film, Corporate film Contact on this number-8130579808 #Apne_log_ngo #ngoinindiaforeducation #biggestngoinindia #ngoinindia #ngonearme #ngonearmetojoin #ngonearmetovolunteer #roleofngoineducationinindia #Street_to_School #Padega_India_To-Badega_India #Education_for_all #Apnelog_cares #Mission_Education #help_the_poor #helping_other #ngo_meaning_in_hindi #ngo_in_delhi_ncr #top_10 _ngo_in_delhi_ncr #how_to_join_ngo_in_delhi web site https://www.apnelog.org Writer,Editor,Director- Raj Kumar #Bhawna_Media For making documentary film, Corporate film Contact on this number-8130579808 ...more

It is through education that you can change the world and break out of the cycle of poverty. The National Sample Survey (NSS-2014) shows that more than two crore Indian children still are out of school after 70 years of independence. Besides being denied an education, these children have also lost their childhood because they must work for their livelihood. This disparity is unfair and undemocratic and hence, Apne Log was founded by a group of dedicated people working together to promote free educational opportunities for underprivileged children living on the streets or in slums. As the name suggests, Apne Log is all about our people, our trust, our belief and our common goal. We strive to not only acknowledge the dire need to educate our children, but also leave no stone unturned to catering to all their needs regardless of their financial circumstances. We are driven by our motto that education is a fundamental right and that no child should be deprived of this right. This ethos has kept our wheels turning for six years now. Over time, education has become institutionalized and commodified.
